                              el-sprunge
                command line paste server run in Emacs

Run the server with the following.

    make start

Optionally set the server name and port using environment variables.

    make start PORT=9090 SERVER=localhost

Optionally specify an Emacs color theme.  To ensure the theme works it
may be necessary to explicitly set the TERM environment variable.

    make start PORT=9090 SERVER=localhost THEME=tango TERM=xterm-256color

The `el-sprunge-after-save-hook' may be used to run actions on every
pasted file.  For example evaluating the following in the Emacs server
will add every new paste to a git repository `el-sprunge-docroot'.

    (require 'vc)
    (defun el-sprunge-vc-add ()
      (ignore-errors
        (let ((file (buffer-file-name (current-buffer))))
          (unless (vc-backend file) (vc-register))
          (vc-checkin (list file) (vc-backend file) nil "a paste"))))
    (add-hook 'el-sprunge-after-save-hook 'el-sprunge-vc-add)
